  "id": "019d2435-73f5-75f3-a360-d4c32f6f9425",
  "content": "# Hook System Rust Migration — Final Decisions (2026-03-25)\n\n## Approved Architecture\n\n1. **Single Rust entry point**: `corvia hooks run --event <type> [--handler <name>]`\n2. **JSONL WAL**: Always write events to ~/.claude/sessions/{session_id}.jsonl with session_id from stdin JSON (not shared file)\n3. **No server POST per hook**: Server watches JSONL directory via inotify for real-time dashboard updates\n4. **No telemetry init in CLI**: Embed telemetry-ready fields (hook_duration_ms, hook_status, hook_name) in JSONL events. Derive spans during ingestion.\n5. **No custom hook dispatch**: Cut permanently. Claude Code settings.json handles arbitrary commands natively.\n6. **Orphan cleanup in Rust**: Zero new deps (std::fs + libc::kill). Must handle sessions that never get SessionEnd (/clear, auto-compact, long sessions).\n7. **Doc-placement in Rust**: Matcher stays in settings.json (Write|Edit). Rules from corvia.toml.\n8. **Schema versioning**: \"v\": 1 on every JSONL event from day 1.\n9. **Drop turn counter file**: Derive turn from JSONL user_prompt count during ingestion.\n10. **Drop .current-session-id file**: Use session_id from Claude Code stdin JSON on every invocation.\n11. **Atomic JSONL writes**: Write to buffer, single append. No partial lines on SIGTERM.\n12. **init-hooks atomic replace**: Remove old bash entries, add Rust entries, preserve user's non-corvia hooks. Idempotent.\n\n## Critical Design Constraint\n\nUser runs very long sessions, often without SessionEnd (/clear, auto-compact). Implications:\n- Orphan cleanup cannot rely solely on SessionEnd — needs periodic/startup trigger too\n- JSONL files may never be gzipped — ingestion must handle raw .jsonl files\n- Session data must be durable even without a clean shutdown\n- Consider: corvia-dev post-start.sh can sweep stale sessions on workspace startup\n\n## Handlers (all in Rust)\n\n| Handler | Event | Matcher | Behavior |\n|---------|-------|---------|----------|\n| session-record | All events | (none) | Atomic JSONL append |\n| doc-placement | PreToolUse | Write\\|Edit | Validate path, exit 0/2 |\n| corvia-first-reminder | PreToolUse | Grep\\|Glob | Echo reminder |\n| write-reminder | PostToolUse | Bash | Check git commit, echo reminder |\n| agent-check | SessionStart | (none) | POST /agents/connect, graceful fallback |\n| orphan-cleanup | SessionEnd | (none) | Kill orphaned processes, WSL cache drop |\n| session-finalize | SessionEnd | (none) | Gzip JSONL, bounded retry ingest |\n\n## Config in corvia.toml\n\n```toml\n[hooks]\nsession_recording = true\ndoc_placement = true\nagent_check = true\nwrite_reminder = true\norphan_cleanup = true\ncorvia_first_reminder = true\n```",
  "source_version": "mcp",
